(48, 48, '【灵异鬼事】一听就上瘾的鬼故事', 'https://fdfs.xmcdn.com/group60/M09/7C/73/wKgLeVy-zQKjOanyAASU4wIo8VY445.jpg', '专辑简介： 一听就上瘾的鬼故事，本专辑包涵了校园、民间、都市、医院、个人真实经历的鬼故事，你想要的，我这儿都有！投稿交流vx：ytgs5588主播简介： 雨田故事：喜马拉雅独家签约主播，凭借低沉磁性的嗓音，生动形象的演播，短时间内获得几十万的忠实粉丝。本专辑最为主播的第一部作品，前后故事录制的时间跨度比较大，从播音小白一路成长到现在的作品都包含在内了。听到不得劲儿的地方多多包涵，主播也在努力成长。喜欢主播讲故事，麻烦给主播点个关注，订阅支持一下！每周定期更新。谢谢大家！', 'Entertainment', 'www.644283488@qq.com', '专辑简介： 一听就上瘾的鬼故事，本专辑包涵了校园、民间、都市、医院、个人真实经历的鬼故事，你想要的，我这儿都有！投稿交流vx：ytgs5588主播简介： 雨田故事：喜马拉雅独家签约主播，凭借低沉磁性的嗓音，生动形象的演播，短时间内获得几十万的忠实粉丝。本专辑最为主播的第一部作品，前后故事录制的时间跨度比较大，从播音小白一路成长到现在的作品都包含在内了。听到不得劲儿的地方多多包涵，主播也在努力成长。喜欢主播讲故事，麻烦给主播点个关注，订阅支持一下！每周定期更新。谢谢大家！', '【灵异鬼事】一听就上瘾的鬼故事', 'https://www.ximalaya.com/album/17015854.xml', '2.8', 0, '0', 0, '2020-10-23'),
(49, 49, 'Talk Is Jericho', 'https://images.megaphone.fm/3W3Vio1DNlN8zfN1IoPKAX866sB5X8097PYZaBxMcUg/plain/s3://megaphone-prod/podcasts/d6463894-9b7a-11ea-bc7d-f378ac2964f6/image/image.jpg', 'He’s a multiple world champion pro wrestler, lead singer of Fozzy, and a New York Times best-selling author. Listen in as Chris Jericho interviews some of the biggest names in wrestling, entertainment, comedy, and the paranormal. Don’t miss his unique, engaging, weekly take on all things pop culture.', 'Sports', 'wwopodcasts@westwoodone.com', 'He’s a multiple world champion pro wrestler, lead singer of Fozzy, and a New York Times best-selling author. Listen in as Chris Jericho interviews some of the biggest names in wrestling, entertainment, comedy, and the paranormal. Don’t miss his unique, engaging, weekly take on all things pop culture.', 'Recorded from all over the globe, multiple time world champion pro wrestler, lead singer of Fozzy and New York Times best-selling author Chris Jericho rocks the podcast world with \"Talk Is Jericho,\" his unique, weekly take...', 'https://feeds.megaphone.fm/WWO9741031485', '3.8', 0, '0', 0, '2020-10-23'),
(50, 50, 'Football Ramble', 'https://thumborcdn.acast.com/p_MncCJBzqPRpcryYQ1Bw7zh088=/1500x1500/https://mediacdn.acast.com/assets/8af0c347-5e6e-48e2-8fae-3f4e765c84ab/-kecw4er5-footballramble_showartwork.jpg', '<p>In 2007, The Football Ramble was born out of Luke Moore, Pete Donaldson, Marcus Speller and Jim Campbell’s passion for the most popular sport in the world—as well as a shared inability to take themselves too seriously. Since then, the boys have come a very long way: from a best-selling book to sold out live shows.</p><p><br></p><p>Now, with the return of football post-lockdown, the Football Ramble brings you daily episodes of equal parts insight and hilarity. All this and more, Monday through Saturday. Lend us your ears and we’ll keep you up to date with the latest stories from the Premier League and all around Europe, all with an eye for both the sublime and the ridiculous.</p>', 'Sports', 'show@footballramble.com', 'In 2007, The Football Ramble was born out of Luke Moore, Pete Donaldson, Marcus Speller and Jim Campbell’s passion for the most popular sport in the world—as well as a shared inability to take themselves too seriously. Since then, the boys have come a very long way: from a best-selling book to sold out live shows.\n\n\nNow, with the return of football post-lockdown, the Football Ramble brings you daily episodes of equal parts insight and hilarity. All this and more, Monday through Saturday. Lend us your ears and we’ll keep you up to date with the latest stories from the Premier League and all around Europe, all with an eye for both the sublime and the ridiculous.', 'The Football Ramble emerged from London towards the end of 2007 as a genuinely refreshing football voice, and quickly established itself as one of the most influential and entertaining shows about the world&apos;s most popular sport. ', 'https://rss.acast.com/footballramble', '1.9', 0, '0', 0, '2020-10-23'),
(51, 51, 'The Sky Sports Football Podcast', 'https://d3wo5wojvuv7l.cloudfront.net/t_rss_itunes_square_1400/images.spreaker.com/original/6ea89705f49ea1e7d9756ed1dafc198e.jpg', 'The twists, turns and major talking points of the football season analysed by Sky Sports’ expert pundits and reporters, including Gary Neville, Jamie Carragher, and Jamie Redknapp.', 'Sports', 'skysportspodcasts@sky.uk', 'The twists, turns and major talking points of the football season analysed by Sky Sports’ expert pundits and reporters, including Gary Neville, Jamie Carragher, and Jamie Redknapp.', 'The twists, turns and major talking points of the football season analysed by Sky Sports’ expert pundits and reporters, including Gary Neville, Jamie Carragher, and Jamie Redknapp.', 'https://podcast.global.com/show/3382902/episodes/feed', '3.1', 0, '0', 0, '2020-10-23'),
(52, 52, 'THEMOVE', 'https://ssl-static.libsyn.com/p/assets/0/6/8/a/068a9fff4dbfa68a/THEMOVE_2000pix.jpg', 'Lance Armstrong presents a singular perspective on the world’s most iconic cycling races, including the Tour de France and the Classics, as well as the broader endurance sports scene. Not your typical cycling or sports podcast, THEMOVE brings listeners deep inside the racing action, imparting insights from someone who knows the suffering and splendor like no one else. In addition to  course previews and timely race analysis from Armstrong’s distinct point of view, the audience also gets to hear from featured guests, who regularly swing by the THEMOVE studio to join the always-lively conversation. Guests have included former teammates like George Hincapie during the Tour de France, and Mark Allen and Dave Scott in advance of the IRONMAN World Championship. \r\n\r\nTHEMOVE is an audio-video experience that transforms every listener from fan and spectator into the ultimate insider.', 'Sports', 'higs@wedu.team', 'Lance Armstrong presents a singular perspective on the world’s most iconic cycling races, including the Tour de France and the Classics, as well as the broader endurance sports scene. Not your typical cycling or sports podcast, THEMOVE brings listeners deep inside the racing action, imparting insights from someone who knows the suffering and splendor like no one else. In addition to  course previews and timely race analysis from Armstrong’s distinct point of view, the audience also gets to hear from featured guests, who regularly swing by the THEMOVE studio to join the always-lively conversation. Guests have included former teammates like George Hincapie during the Tour de France, and Mark Allen and Dave Scott in advance of the IRONMAN World Championship. \r\n\r\nTHEMOVE is an audio-video experience that transforms every listener from fan and spectator into the ultimate insider.', '', 'https://stages.libsyn.com/rss', '3.8', 0, '0', 0, '2020-10-23'),
(53, 53, 'Athletico Mince', 'https://thumborcdn.acast.com/msLtgjVYQISbWuQf0B_E9uMYWXs=/1500x1500/https://mediacdn.acast.com/assets/512e6e5b-1328-4152-869e-16ad11c71e70/-k7v2fx8q-athletico-mince-1400x1400-no_balls.png', '<p>Bob Mortimer and Andy Dawson\'s podcast - brass hands, blue drink and more. It\'s not really about football, d\'you know what I mean?</p>', 'Entertainment', 'profanityswan@gmail.com', 'Bob Mortimer and Andy Dawson\'s podcast - brass hands, blue drink and more. It\'s not really about football, d\'you know what I mean?', 'Bob Mortimer and Andy Dawson&apos;s podcast - brass hands, blue drink and more. It&apos;s not really about football, d&apos;you know what I mean?', 'https://rss.acast.com/athleticomince', '2.8', 0, '0', 0, '2020-10-23'),
(54, 54, '31 Thoughts: The Podcast', 'https://podcast.sportsnet.ca/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/31-Thoughts_3000x3000.jpg', 'Jeff Marek and Elliotte Friedman talk to a lot of people around the hockey world, and then they tell listeners all about what they’ve heard and what they think about it.  Plus, look for bonus episodes featuring interviews with personalities in the game or famous fans.', 'Sports', 'Sportsnet.Podcasts@rci.rogers.com', 'Hockey fans already know the name, but this is not the blog. From Sportsnet, 31 Thoughts: The Podcast is a weekly deep dive into the biggest hockey news in the world, featuring Jeff Marek and NHL Insider Elliotte Friedman.', '<p>A weekly deep dive into the biggest hockey news in the world, featuring Jeff Marek and NHL Insider Elliotte Friedman.</p> <p>31 Thoughts: The Podcast is presented by the all-new 2018 GMC Terrain.</p>', 'https://podcast.sportsnet.ca/shows/31-thoughts/feed/podcast/', '3.9', 0, '0', 0, '2020-10-23'),
(55, 55, 'Arseblog - the Arsecasts, Arsenal podcasts', 'https://thumborcdn.acast.com/HWbw_C6VISLsqiKJdgffqOGyyXE=/1500x1500/https://mediacdn.acast.com/assets/a1a58121-6fb4-43cf-8156-8d6df6fc312f/-jf3si70l-arsecast_itunes_new.jpg', '<p>The original Arsenal podcast - coming to you twice a week (Mondays and Fridays) with news, interviews, analysis, special guests, jokes and occasionally some really terrible songs.</p>', 'Sports', 'andrew@arseblog.com', 'A podcast/arsecast from www.arseblog.com about Arsenal football club', 'The Arsecast - the original, award winning Arsenal podcast', 'https://rss.acast.com/arseblog', '4.2', 0, '0', 0, '2020-10-23'),
